<h3>Using the FishTales Form</h3>
<p>The FishTales interface allows you to configure report scraping and summarization. Default values are provided for convenience, but can be adjusted as needed.</p>

<h5>Basic Inputs</h5>

<ul>
    <li>
        <strong>Gemini API Key:</strong>  Enter your private API key in the field provided.<br>
        <em>Note:</em> This is required for FishTales to access Gemini AI models.
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Max Report Age:</strong> Specify the maximum age of reports in days.<br>
        <em>Default:</em> <code>100</code>
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Filter by Rivers:</strong> Enable to restrict reports to specific rivers.<br>
        <em>Default:</em> <code>false</code>
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>River Names</strong> (<em>Optional</em>): Enter a comma-separated list of river names.
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Starter File</strong>: Import your current dataset, or use the
        <a href="/example_files/report_starter_file_ex.xlsx" download><strong>example file</strong></a>.
    </li>
</ul>

